  "timeframe": "1H",
  "market_context": "Imperfect uptrend with choppy price action; analyst evaluates whether a recent swing high qualifies as a major swing to determine if a break above it constitutes a valid change of character.",
  "key_observation": "The recent impulsive move pushed only 20 pips, while the prior impulsive move was over 60 pips; insufficient distance means the recent swing high is not a major swing, so breaking above it does not signal a true reversal.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Analyst identifies a recent downward impulsive move that created a new swing high and broke structure to the downside.",
    "Step 2: Analyst measures the distance of the prior impulsive move (over 60 pips) and compares it to the recent impulsive move (only 20 pips).",
    "Step 3: Analyst applies the distance criterion: a swing qualifies as major only if the impulse distance is at least half of the previous impulsive move’s distance.",
    "Step 4: Analyst concludes the recent swing high fails the distance test, so it is not a major swing, and thus a break above it does not constitute a valid change of character."
  ],
  "outcome": null,
  "lessons": "A swing point must satisfy three criteria—break of structure, imbalance (FVG), and sufficient impulse distance (≥50% of prior impulse)—to be considered a major swing; lacking any one invalidates its significance for trend reversal signals.",
